
[1]benevolence

   BENEV'OLENCE, n. [L. benevolentia, of bene, well and volo, to will or
   wish. See Will.]

   1. The disposition to do good; good will; kindness; charitableness; the
   love,of mankind, accompanied with a desire to promote their happiness.

   The benevolence of God is one of his moral attributes; that attribute
   which delights in the happiness of intelligent beings. "God is love." 1
   John 4.

   2. An act of kindness; good done; charity given.

   3. A species of contribution or tax illegally exacted by arbitrary
   kings of England.
